# Resurrection Agent cron schedule (America/New_York)
#
# Install on the primary host (where the agent lives Mon-Fri-3:59pm):
#   crontab -e
#   # then paste:
#
# Fri 16:00 EST: kill the agent, wipe local state
#   0 16 * * 5 cd $HOME/ensoul/packages/resurrection-agent && ./scripts/kill.sh >> $HOME/.ensoul/resurrection-agent/kill.log 2>&1
#
# Install on the SECONDARY host (the one that picks up after kill):
#   Fri 16:05 EST: resurrect on new machine
#   5 16 * * 5 cd $HOME/ensoul/packages/resurrection-agent && ./scripts/resurrect.sh >> $HOME/.ensoul/resurrection-agent/resurrect.log 2>&1
#
# To alternate hosts week-over-week, have the resurrect.sh script include
# a hostname-rotation hop that scp's the vault to the next-next machine.
# For MVP, just alternate between MBP and one of the Minis manually.
#
# Note: cron runs in local system timezone by default. Set TZ at the top
# of crontab if your box is not in America/New_York:
#   TZ=America/New_York
